cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MM

This paper deals with radio resource management for D2D-based V2V communications, which involves network protocols, wireless communication, and system optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) as possible categories. The paper also discusses interference and security issues, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper includes simulations to illustrate the proposed method, which could be related to cs.MM (Multimedia).
